Several municipalities are warning staff that they might not get paid this month. JOHANNESBURG - Several municipalities are warning staff that they might not get paid this month. National Treasury is withholding funds over non-compliance as part of the Municipal Finance Management Act.
The Bojanala Platinum District Municipality says salaries for July will be delayed and that it's engaging with Treasury to resolve the matter. READ: Dlamini-Zuma responds to Auditor-General's report The Maluti-a-Phofung Local Municipality in the Free State is in a similar situation. The district has been unable to convene a council to elect office-bearers. The Auditor-General's report for the 2017/2018 year revealed that only 18 municipalities had clean audits.